'''傑拉爾丁·霍夫·道爾'''（{{lang-en|Geraldine Hoff Doyle}}；{{bd|1924年|7月31日|2010年|12月26日}}）是一名[[美國|美國]]女性。在2000年代曾被大眾普遍認為是宣傳海報《[[我們能做到！|我們能做到！]]》所描繪的[[鉚釘女工|鉚釘女工]]的原型人物。在她死後，經過後續調查發現另一名女工[[娜歐蜜·帕克·弗雷利|娜歐蜜·帕克·弗雷利]]才更有可能是真正的原型<ref name=Kimble2016>{{cite journal |title=Rosie's Secret Identity, or, How to Debunk a Woozle by Walking Backward through the Forest of Visual Rhetoric |last=Kimble |first=James J. |date=Summer 2016 |journal=Rhetoric and Public Affairs |volume=19 |number=2 |pages=245–274 |issn=1094-8392}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2010/12/30/132484640/michigan-woman-who-inspired-wwii-rosie-poster-has-died |title=Michigan Woman Who Inspired WWII 'Rosie' Poster Has Died : The Two-Way : NPR |date=2015-09-09 |access-date=2016-03-01  |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150909011757/http://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2010/12/30/132484640/michigan-woman-who-inspired-wwii-rosie-poster-has-died |archivedate=2015-09-09 }}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web| url = http://museum.nps.gov/ParkObjdet.aspx?rID=RORI%20%20%20%203610%26db%3Dobjects%26dir%3DCR%20AAWEB%26page%3D1| title = Museum Collections, U.S. National Park Service -| website = museum.nps.gov| access-date = 2016-03-01| archive-date = 2016-03-07| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160307094053/http://museum.nps.gov/ParkObjdet.aspx?rID=RORI%2520%2520%2520%25203610%2526db%253Dobjects%2526dir%253DCR%2520AAWEB%2526page%253D1}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web| url = http://www.corbisimages.com/stock-photo/rights-managed/42-62386550/all-this-and-overtime-too?popup=1| title = All This and Overtime, Too - 42-62386550 - Rights Managed - Stock Photo - Corbis| website = www.corbisimages.com| access-date = 2016-03-01| archive-date = 2015-11-12| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151112182920/http://www.corbisimages.com/stock-photo/rights-managed/42-62386550/all-this-and-overtime-too?popup=1}}</ref>。這場誤會被認為是[[三人成虎|三人成虎]]的經典案例。

== 生平 ==
[[Image:We_Can_Do_It!_NARA_535413_-_Restoration_2.jpg|upright]]》]]
傑拉爾丁·霍夫出生於[[密西根州|密西根州]]{{link-en|英克斯特 (密西根州)|Inkster, Michigan|英克斯特}}，她的父親寇納利耶司（Cornelious）是一名[[電工|電工]]，在她十歲時死於[[肺炎|肺炎]]。母親奧古斯塔（Augusta）是一名[[作曲家|作曲家]]，患有[[脊椎側彎|脊椎側彎]]。1942年，傑拉爾丁從[[安娜堡|安娜堡]]的一所高中畢業，並在當地的製造商「American Broach & Machine Co.」找到一份工作，負責操作[[衝壓|金屬衝壓機台]]<ref name=latimes /><ref name=":3">[http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/northjersey/obituary.aspx?n=geraldine-doyle&pid=147504997 Geraldine Doyle: Obituary] {{Wayback|url=http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/northjersey/obituary.aspx?n=geraldine-doyle&pid=147504997 |date=20210429150825 }} - legacy.com</ref>。

由於傑拉爾丁也有在拉[[大提琴|大提琴]]，她擔心操作機台可能會傷到她寶貴的手指，所以她只工作了幾個禮拜便辭職了<ref name=latimes /><ref name=":4">[http://usnews.nbcnews.com/_news/2010/12/30/5738254-geraldine-doyle-inspiration-for-rosie-the-riveter-dies-at-86?lite Geraldine Doyle, inspiration for 'Rosie the Riveter,' dies at 86] {{Wayback|url=http://usnews.nbcnews.com/_news/2010/12/30/5738254-geraldine-doyle-inspiration-for-rosie-the-riveter-dies-at-86?lite |date=20180202012350 }} published December 30, 2010 by [[NBC_News|NBC News]]: "Geraldine Doyle left her factory job after two weeks"</ref>。根據傑拉爾丁自己的說法，在這短暫的工作期間，曾有一位[[合眾國際社|合眾國際社]]的攝影師替她拍下照片。在傑拉爾丁辭職後隔年，她嫁給牙醫雷歐·H·道爾（Leo H. Doyle），夫妻之間育有六名子女。雷歐死於2010年2月<ref name=latimes />。

2010年12月26日，傑拉爾丁·霍夫·道爾於[[密西根州蘭辛|密西根州蘭辛]]逝世，死因為嚴重[[關節炎|關節炎]]所引發的併發症。到死為止她都還被普遍認為是《我們能做到！》海報的原型人物<ref name=latimes>{{cite news|first=Dennis|last=McLellan|url=http://www.latimes.com/news/obituaries/la-me-geraldine-hoff-doyle-20101231,0,1376340.story|title=Geraldine Hoff Doyle dies at 86; inspiration behind a famous wartime poster|work=Los Angeles Times|date=2010-12-31|accessdate=2010-12-31|archive-date=2012-09-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120920115125/http://www.latimes.com/news/obituaries/la-me-geraldine-hoff-doyle-20101231%2C0%2C1376340.story}}</ref><ref name="WashingtonPost">{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/12/29/AR2010122905336_pf.html|title=Geraldine Doyle, 86, dies; one-time factory worker inspired Rosie the Riveter and 'We Can Do It!' poster|work=The Washington Post|date=2011-12-29|accessdate=2012-09-06|author=Shapiro, T. Rees – Washington Post staff writer|archive-date=2021-02-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210210230923/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/12/29/AR2010122905336_pf.html}}</ref><ref name="Huff">{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2010/12/30/rosie-riveter-dead-geraldine-hoff-doyle_n_802772.html|title=Geraldine Hoff Doyle Dead: 'Rosie The Riveter' Inspiration Dies At 86|accessdate=2011-01-01|work=Huffington Post|first=Hilary|last=Moss|date=2010-12-30|archive-date=2016-12-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161222103353/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2010/12/30/rosie-riveter-dead-geraldine-hoff-doyle_n_802772.html}}</ref>。

== 關於《我們能做到！》海報 ==
<!-- 注释: [[File:Geraldine_Hoff_Doyle.jpg|1942年的照片。傑拉爾丁宣稱自己是照片中的女子，但女子的實際身份應為[[娜歐蜜·帕克·弗雷利]]|thumb|right|upright]] -->
由於《[[我們能做到！|我們能做到！]]》最初並不是發佈給美國大眾，而是[[西屋電氣|西屋電氣]]為了鼓舞自家員工士氣而張貼在工廠內部的海報，所以最一開始並沒有進入大眾視野。一直到[[第二次世界大戰|第二次世界大戰]]結束後的1980年代，該海報才被「職場性別平等」的倡導者重新發現，並將海報用來宣傳其主張。1984年，道爾在《{{link-en|美國退休人協會雜誌|AARP the Magazine}}》上看到照片，是身份不明的年輕女子操作垂直{{link-en|成型機|shaper}}的情景。1994年，道爾又在《[[史密森尼_(雜誌)|史密森尼]]》雜誌上看到《我們能做到！》的海報。照片與海報上的女子都令她聯想到自己<ref name="nbcnews">{{cite news|last=Chuck |first=Elizabeth |title=Geraldine Doyle, inspiration for 'Rosie the Riveter,' dies at 86 |url=http://fieldnotes.msnbc.msn.com/_news/2010/12/30/5738254-geraldine-doyle-inspiration-for-rosie-the-riveter-dies-at-86 |accessdate=2015-07-01 |work=Field Notes from NBC News |date=2010-12-30 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110101123212/http://fieldnotes.msnbc.msn.com/_news/2010/12/30/5738254-geraldine-doyle-inspiration-for-rosie-the-riveter-dies-at-86 |archivedate=2011-01-01 }}</ref>。同樣在1990年代，她與歷史學家兼作家{{link-en|潘妮·科爾曼|Penny Colman}}取得聯繫，並拿出自己的主張與對方交流<ref name=":5">{{Cite web|url=http://www.pennycolman.com/my-books/rosie-the-riveter-image/ |title=Rosie the Riveter Image {{!}} Penny Colman |date=2011-04-28 |access-date=2016-03-02 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110428052725/http://www.pennycolman.com/my-books/rosie-the-riveter-image/ |archivedate=2011-04-28 }}</ref>。道爾的主張很快就被大眾接受，她被普遍認為是海報中[[鉚釘女工|鉚釘女工]]的原型人物<ref name=Kimble2016/> 。她曾被{{link-en|密西根州女性名人堂|Michigan Women's Hall of Fame}}公開紀念，本人還會不時前往名人堂替遊客簽名、作互動。道爾曾表示自己當年對海報一無所知或許是一件好事，「我那時候還沒法處理好這麼令人激動的情況」<ref name="latimes" />。

在道爾死後，許多媒體也將道爾報導為「《我們能做到！》海報的原型人物」，沒有檢驗道爾的主張是否正確<ref name=":2" /><ref name=":3" /><ref name=":4" /><ref name="nbcnews" /><ref name="WashingtonPost" />。2011年，[[娜歐蜜·帕克·弗雷利|娜歐蜜·帕克·弗雷利]]在{{link-en|鉚釘女工第二次世界大戰家庭前線國家歷史公園|Rosie the Riveter World War II Home Front National Historical Park}}舉辦的一場重聚聯歡會中認出自己1942年時的照片<ref name=TIME>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/5114251/rosie-the-riveter-real-identity/|title=Everyone Was Wrong About the Real 'Rosie the Riveter' for Decades. Here’s How the Mystery Was Solved|publisher=Time|accessdate=2018-01-23|date=2018-01-23|archive-date=2020-09-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919104142/https://time.com/5114251/rosie-the-riveter-real-identity/}}</ref>，但卻驚訝地發現照片上標示的人名不是自己，而是道爾<ref name="NPR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2018/01/23/580076619/naomi-parker-fraley-from-rosie-the-riveter-poster-dies-at-96|title=Naomi Parker-Fraley, From Rosie The Riveter Poster, Dies At 96|publisher=NPR|accessdate=2018-01-23|date=2018-01-23|archive-date=2019-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191101100101/https://www.npr.org/2018/01/23/580076619/naomi-parker-fraley-from-rosie-the-riveter-poster-dies-at-96}}</ref>。根據後續研究<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.krcrtv.com/news/local/northstate-woman-shares-experience-as-rosie/37583940|title=Northstate woman shares experience as 'Rosie'|last=KRCR|website=KRCRTV|access-date=2016-03-02|archive-date=2016-05-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160516114230/http://www.krcrtv.com/news/local/northstate-woman-shares-experience-as-rosie/37583940}}</ref>，實際上在1942年3月照片拍攝時，傑拉爾丁·道爾仍就讀高中，她是畢業後才去工廠上班，所以不可能是照片主角<ref name="Today">{{cite web|url=https://www.today.com/news/naomi-parker-fraley-real-life-rosie-riveter-dies-96-t121552|title=Naomi Parker Fraley, the real-life Rosie the Riveter, dies at 96|publisher=Today|accessdate=2018-01-23|date=2018-01-29|archive-date=2019-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122130428/https://www.today.com/news/naomi-parker-fraley-real-life-rosie-riveter-dies-96-t121552}}</ref><ref name=Kimble2016/>。道爾從未宣稱過自己曾與海報設計師J·霍華德·米勒（J. Howard Miller）見過面，僅宣稱自己是1942年那張照片的主角<ref name=":3" /><ref name=":5" />。而無論該張照片的主角是誰，實際上並沒有證據顯示米勒在設計海報時真的有將該照片作為靈感來源<ref name=nyt>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/22/obituaries/naomi-parker-fraley-the-real-rosie-the-riveter-dies-at-96.html|title=Naomi Parker Fraley, the Real Rosie the Riveter, Dies at 96|last=Fox|first=Margalit|date=2018|work=The New York Times|access-date=2018-01-23|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2018-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180122211046/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/22/obituaries/naomi-parker-fraley-the-real-rosie-the-riveter-dies-at-96.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

